# 2026-06-03 — Rebase onto upstream/develop + redeploy + full test run

## Rebase

Rebased `cns/test-foundations` off `upstream/develop` (the project's actual primary branch). The branch was previously based on `upstream/master`, which is now 28+ commits behind develop. Strategy: dropped the master-merge commit and cherry-picked the 11 substantive work commits in chronological order, resolving conflicts as we went.

**Branch state:** 11 clean linear commits on top of `upstream/develop` (HEAD = `5846313` "feat (DT) Build-run tracing in the registry"). Old branch preserved as the local tag `pre-rebase-cns` (`19aed22`) for recovery if needed.

**Notable conflict resolutions during the rebase:**

1. **`pyproject.toml`** — kept develop's `pip-audit>=2.7.0` AND added the CNS test-foundation deps (hypothesis, syrupy, testcontainers[postgres], fastmcp, pyyaml, ruff>=0.7.4, mypy>=1.13.0, pytest-mock).
2. **`uv.lock`** — regenerated via `uv lock` after merging pyproject.
3. **`.cursor/11-` filename collision** — develop has `.cursor/11-frontend-design.mdc`. Renamed CNS rule to `.cursor/12-ai-feature-lifecycle.mdc` and updated 8 referencing files (`.claude/skills/ai-feature/{SKILL,SPEC.template}.md`, `docs/PR_REVIEW_CHECKLIST.md`, `.github/workflows/eval-gate.yml`, `.planning/agents/{README,agent_owl_generator/SPEC}.md`, `.planning/ROADMAP.md`, `src/.coding_rules.md`). Folded into the CNS-foundation commit.
4. **`changelogs/2026-05-14.log`** — dropped the round-6 entry (master-merge no longer applies); rewrote round-7 context line.
5. **`tests/test_settings_lakebase_status.py`** — develop relocated this to `tests/units/settings/test_settings_lakebase_status.py`. Git's rename-detection applied the psycopg-stub fix to the correct path.
6. **`tests/back/core/digitaltwin/test_build_pipeline_units.py`** — `_BuildPipeline.__init__` signature is simpler on develop (no `stored_source_versions`, `force_full`, `config_changed`, `snapshot_version`, `archive_to_registry`; no `actual_mode`/`cfg_forced_full` attributes). Rewrote 15 tests to match develop's API; landed 16/16 green. Fixup folded into the round-7 commit via `git rebase --autosquash`.

